Stop-limit order: a combo order of a stop order and a limit order. 

Why stop-limit order: Allow traders to precisely control when to execute the order. It is often used to lock in profits or limit downside risks.

3/

Stop-market order: order will execute once a set price has been reached, then fill at the current market price.

Why stop-market order: Allow traders to quickly lock in profits or limit downside risks.

2/ 

Limit order: Allows traders to set a maximum acceptable buy price or a minimum acceptable sales price.

Why limit order: Limit order provides better control over price. Therefore, it is beneficial when the trading pairs are volatile, illiquid, and widely spread.
